ce:section.ce:para:
The three functionalized GQDs were prepared by a modified nanocutting method from carbon fiber and using H2SO4/HNO3. The hydrodynamic size of the non-functionalized GQDs was 122 nm, whereas that of the hydroxylated and carboxylated GQDs was 190 nm (Table 1
                     ). However, the actual size of the GQDs is around 5 nm (Nurunnabi et al., 2013c). The UV and PL properties of the three functionalized GQDs were measured as well. The UV visible absorption and photoluminescence spectra of the three functionalized GQDs are shown in Fig. 1
                     . According to UV analysis, a distinct absorption peak around 280 nm was observed due to the π-π* vibration of aromatic groups, and a long tail extended into the visible range. When the non-functionalized, hydroxylated, and carboxylated GQDs were excited using a 365 nm UV lamp, these GQDs emitted yellow, blue, and green luminescence, which was bright enough to be observed by the naked eye; this indicated the promising potential of the GQDs for use in various application including biomedicine. These GQDs disperse well in water with high stability (Nurunnabi et al., 2013c, 2013b, 2013a) and have strong photoluminescence intensity. The non-functionalized, hydroxylated, and carboxylated GQDs emitted luminescence at 500 nm, 350 nm, and 425 nm, respectively.
